ShillerRepresentativenessTest::shillerCore
├── when a standardized cpi surprise is derived
│   └── it equals actual minus consensus over sigma in wad with the sign preserved
├── when a surprise magnitude is mapped to a convex option ratio
│   └── it is convex monotone in the absolute surprise clamped between one and one hundred twenty seven
├── when a strike tick is derived from a signed surprise
│   └── it is sign driven and tickspacing aligned around the pke anchor
├── when a chunk width is derived from a surprise magnitude
│   └── it is even snapped and non decreasing with at least one strict widening step
└── when the surprise oracle is stale or unset
    ├── given observedAt is zero
    │   └── it maps to the zero surprise minimal stance
    └── given observedAt is beyond the max staleness window
        └── it maps to the zero surprise minimal stance
